THE date for the motion of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma has been revised to August 8, Parliament announced earlier today.&nbsp; In a statement, it said the Speaker of the National Assembly had decided to revise the date after consultation with political parties in Parliament and with the Executive.&nbsp; The date was previously set as August 3.&nbsp; "There was an oversight during the initial consultations and determination of the originally announced date, which overlooked the fact that a Cabinet Lekgotla had already been set for that week. &ldquo;The deadline for political parties to submit their views regarding their preferred means of voting on this particular Motion, that is, whether by a secret or open ballot, remains July 14, 2017.&rdquo;&nbsp; Parliament said the Speaker will make her decision on voting procedure before August 8.